(0000000404, 0000000025, 0000000002, 0000000002, ''),
(0000000404, 0000000025, 0000000003, 0000000001, 'If working with components still is too limiting a custom page can be created.\r\nThis might be needed if the browser must serve something else than html (e.g. a generated csv file).\r\nIn such cases a custom header must be created which interferes with the provided functionality to create html pages.\r\n\r\nThe solution is to create a new page of type **Custom**.\r\nThis can be done via the CMS when enabling the checkbox **Advanced**.\r\nA custom page expects a function with the name `create_\'page_keyword\'_page` where `\'page_keyword\'` is the keyword of the custom page.\r\nThis function must be defined in the file `index.php`.\r\nThe function receives the following parameters:\r\n - `$router`: The router instance which is used to generate valid links (see class [Router](https://selfhelp.psy.unibe.ch/demo/doc/doxygen/html/classRouter.html)).\r\n - `$db`: The instance of the database handler which grants access to the DB and provides useful methods to access data (see class [PageDb](https://selfhelp.psy.unibe.ch/demo/doc/doxygen/html/classPageDb.html)).\r\n - any number of get parameters as defined by the url pattern (refer to the documentation of [Altorouter](http://altorouter.com/) for an overview of available options).\r\n\r\nTo keep things ordered, this function should create an instance of a new custom page class.\r\nPage classes are stored in the path `server/page` and it is recommended to create the new page class in this folder.'),
